National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: HIGHWOOD, MT
Accident Number: DEN90LA083
Date & Time: 04/02/1990, 0930 MDT
Registration: N87BS
Aircraft: PETERSON KIT FOX MODEL 1
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event:
Injuries: 1 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Personal
 Analysis THE PILOT REPORTED THAT SHORTLY AFTER LIFT-OFF, THE AIRPLANE ROLLED LEFT AND THAT THERE WAS INSUFFICIENT AIRSPEED TO ROLL THE WINGS LEVEL.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: A PREMATURE LIFT-OFF BY THE PILOT, RESULTING IN A STALL/MUSH.
Findings Occurrence #1: LOSS OF CONTROL - IN FLIGHT Phase of Operation: TAKEOFF - INITIAL CLIMB Findings 1.
(C) LIFT-OFF - PREMATURE - PILOT IN COMMAND 2.
